The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Macron of France and President Trump of the United States during a meeting in Canada. Macron thanked Trump for their open and direct discussion, particularly regarding trade. They expressed a willingness to find agreements and a win-win approach for their people. They also mentioned upcoming discussions on North Korea, Syria, and Iran. Trump thanked Macron for his help in addressing the trade deficit with the European Union and praised his leadership in France. The topic of Russia was not discussed.